Ingredients: 3/4 cup milk, 2 tablespoons white vinegar, 1 cup flour, 2 tablespoons white sugar, 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon baking soda, 1/2 teaspoon salt, 1 egg, 2 tablespoons melted butter, cooking spray.
Step 1: Mix the milk with the vinegar then set aside for about 5 minutes to sour.
Step 2: Combine flour,sugar,salt,baking powder,baking soda, in a large bowl. Then whisk the egg and butter into the soured milk. now pour the dry mixure into the wet mixture and whisk until all lumps are gone.
Step 3: Heat a large pan over medium heat, and spray the pan with cooking spray. Pour about 1/4 cupfuls of batter onto the pan, and cook until bubble appear on the surface. Then flip with a spatula and wait until the other side is brown.
Step 5: Let cool about 2-3 minutes then serve.